for those of you who attend anime conventions what do you like most and least about them i went to afo last week and there were some awesome things and some not so awesome things things that i like at a con people who wear good costumes and know how to pose great special guests more adult themed stuff at night carded of course a convention held at a hotel i can afford to stay at good selection at the dealers room a convention where anime is showed in the hotel rooms things that i do not like at a cons people who fail to take a shower all week none of the events starting on time loud annoying people screaming things like cute in japanese and running me over to glomp their friends of the same character series running around very much old school anime being showed so what is everyone else's take on anime conventions what do you go for what do you know will happen that you dread p i want to hear other con goers experiences rules for all conventions good thing haggling with people on the merchant floors bad thing haggling with people on the merchant floors when there a bunch of people in line behind you to make purchases good thing taking in a lecture bad thing taking in a lecture and spending the whole time talking with your friends talking on the cell phone good thing meeting celebrities bad thing meeting celebrities then expecting to monopolize their time good thing previewing upcoming products bad thing the people that love absolutely every new product they see good thing learning more about the culture bad thing learning more about the culture so you can be a culture snob good thing being with a social group bad thing being with a social group and doing antisocial things like spending the whole time not showering or sulking up in your room good thing finding someone with similar interests for a date bad thing finding someone with similar interests for a date then finding out you have nothing else in common besides the interests at the con i could go on but that's a 